There's an already existing state that represents whether or not the timer is running. To start the timer when the user clicks the start button, you should change the value of this state, so that other parts of your code will "know" that the timer should start running.  

🚨 Spoiler alert! Want more hints? ️️⬇️ Scroll down to line 50 🚨














































 Your code should "know" whether or not the timer should be running based on whether timerRunning === true or false. It should be set to true when the user clicks the start button. You can then build the rest of your logic around the value of timerRunning. 